      <pubtit><font size="4">Embeddings in ‚Äúrandom like‚Äù graphs</font></pubtit>
      <p><em><strong>Abstract: </strong></em>An archetype problem in extremal combinatorics is to study the structure of subgraphs appearing in different classes of (hyper)graphs. We will focus on such embedding problems in ‚Äúrandom like‚Äù graphs. In practice, we will mention ramsey-turan problems and related results.</p>
